16/10/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- The IMF on Wednesday (15 October) praised the government's efforts to conduct structural reforms and its success in curbing inflation and lowering interest rates.
Reza Moghadam, the IMF official responsible for Turkey, spoke at the end of an IMF mission to Ankara that is expected to recommend the release of another $500m in loans under the country's three-year agreement with the Fund.
Turkish Economy Minister Ali Babacan told reporters that the government is confident that it would bring inflation down to 20 per cent, coupled with economic growth of five per cent in 2003.
(AFP - 15/10/03)
